Help text: Please read the README.md file in the GitHub repository for a better looking help text: https://github.com/TheCool1James/AlgorithmaProject/tree/master/SVGtoTuring/README.md
1. You need to create your SVG file first. I reccomend using http://www.drawsvg.org/ as this application was designed around it. Please make sure all the coordinates are integers by enabling grid, and setting decimal places to 0 in drawsvg.org 2. Export the SVG. Rotations and bezier curves are not supported. Please ensure all coordinates are integers for maximum accuracy. 3. Colour will be in RGB. Your teacher may not like this. 4. Export by clicking "Show Code"
How to use http://www.drawsvg.org/ : Under the Document menu, click Open. Open up your comic. Choose "Its real size" under "Edit your document with." Under the "Dimensions" menu, click "Grid." Make sure the grid is 1 px wide, ENABLED AND DISPLAYED. DECIMAL DIGITS MUST BE 0.
